}

title Installed Apps Retrieval Flow

|Client|
start
:Send **GET /installedApps/**\n(subdomain: api)\nQuery params: { orderBy, desc, page, limit };

|InstalledAppsController|
:Extract **actor** from req.actor;

if (actor present?) then (no)
    :Throw **HttpError(401)**\n"actor not found in context";
    stop
else (yes)
endif

if (actor.type.app is set?) then (yes)
    :Throw **HttpError(403)**\n"Apps are not allowed\nto access this resource";
    stop
else (no)
endif

:Apply default **orderBy = 'installed_at'**\nif not provided in query;

if (orderBy in ALLOWED_ORDER_BY?\n['id','name','uid','title','installed_at']) then (no)
    :Throw **HttpError(400)**\n"Invalid orderBy field";
    stop
else (yes)
endif

:Compute **pagination**\npage = max(req.query.page \|\| 1, 1)\nlimit = clamp(req.query.limit \|\| 100, 1, 100)\noffset = (page - 1) × limit;

:Resolve **orderByField** via ORDER_BY_FIELD_MAP\nResolve **sortDirection** ('ASC' | 'DESC')\nfrom req.query.desc;

|Database (BaseDatabaseAccessService)|
:Execute **SQL query** (async)\nSELECT apps.name, uid, title,\ndescription, icon,\nMIN(perm.dt) AS installed_at\nFROM apps\nLEFT JOIN user_to_app_permissions\nWHERE perm.user_id = ?\nGROUP BY apps.id\nORDER BY {orderByField} {sortDirection}\nLIMIT ? OFFSET ?\nParams: [actor.user.id, limit, offset];

|InstalledAppsController|
:Map each **app row**:\nadd **iconUrl = getAppIconUrl(app);**;

|Client|
:Receive response\n**Array of** { name, uid, title,\ndescription, icon,\ninstalled_at, iconUrl };
stop

@enduml
